FBIS4-20536 "jpest008___94032" JPRS-EST-94-008 JPRS Science & Technology Europe/International Economic Competitiveness 14 February 1994 WEST EUROPE CORPORATE ALLIANCES Co-Chairmen Appointed for French-German Telecom Joint Co-Chairmen Appointed for French-German Telecom Joint Venture BR1003090694 Chichester INTERNATIONAL TELECOMMUNICATIONS INTELLIGENCE in English 14 Feb 94 p20 BR1003090694 Chichester INTERNATIONAL TELECOMMUNICATIONS INTELLIGENCE English BFN [Unattributed Article: "France Telecom and Deutsche Bundespost Telekom Announce Appointment of Co-Chairmen for Joint Venture"] [Text] France Telecom and Deutsche Bundespost Telekom have announced the appointment of Jean Arnould and Norbert Knoppik as co-Chairmen of the business communications joint-venture they announced in December last year. The yet-to-be named joint-venture, to be headquartered in Brussels, will provide telecommunications services for multinational corporations, as well as companies and business users involved in international activities. It is expected to become operational in early 1995 and in the first year of operation the two partners expect it to generate some ECU1.5 billion in revenues. The venture will make approximately ECU 1,000 million in investments during the next five years and its workforce will number 4,000 persons. Jean Arnould has worked at France Telecom since 1975 when he was head of Industrial Development within the International Affairs division. He was subsequently appointed Regional Director for Alsace, Lorraine, Nord Pas-de-Calais and Rhones-Alpes. Since 1993, he has been Deputy Director for the Southeast France Sector. Dr. Knoppik joined DBT in 1990 as Head of the Satellite and International Cable Systems Division. He played a decisive role in the development of the Trans-Europe Line (TEL) cable system project and is currently Head of DBT's International Networks Division.
